@startuml
title WhisperX RCA Observability Container View

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left

rectangle "Operator" as Operator
rectangle "WhisperX Trace Wrapper\nscripts/trace-whisperx-rocprof.sh" as Wrapper
rectangle "WhisperX Harness\nscripts/whisperx_rca_harness.py" as Harness
rectangle "rocprofv3 / rocprofiler-sdk" as Profiler
rectangle "Host Watchers\nheartbeat + cpu + devcoredump" as Watchers
rectangle "Kernel / Driver\namdgpu + KFD + journal + devcoredump" as Kernel
rectangle "Retained Evidence Bundle\nout/whisperx-trace/<stamp>" as Bundle

Operator --> Wrapper : starts reduced RCA lane
Wrapper --> Harness : stage-controlled workload
Wrapper --> Profiler : optional profiler backend
Wrapper --> Watchers : low-noise side channel
Harness --> Bundle : events.jsonl\nrun-config.json
Profiler --> Bundle : marker and kernel traces\nif flush survives reset
Watchers --> Bundle : heartbeat.log\nhost-cpu.log\ndevcoredump-watch.log
Kernel --> Bundle : indirect evidence via watcher capture
Harness --> Kernel : GPU work submission
Profiler --> Kernel : profiler instrumentation

note right of Profiler
Crashy runs can lose structured profiler output
if reset lands before profiler finalize/flush.
end note

note bottom of Watchers
Breadcrumb channel should stay cheap and line-buffered.
It is not the primary kernel-attribution surface.
end note

@enduml
